theorem Topology.interior_diff_interior_eq_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    interior (A \ interior A) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- We show that `interior (A \ interior A)` is empty.
    intro x hx
    -- `interior (A \ interior A)` is open and contained in `A`.
    have h_open : IsOpen (interior (A \ interior A)) := isOpen_interior
    have h_subsetA : (A \ interior A) ⊆ A := Set.diff_subset
    have h_into_intA :
        interior (A \ interior A) ⊆ interior A :=
      interior_maximal h_subsetA h_open
    -- Membership of `x` in the interior of the difference yields a contradiction.
    have hx_in_intA : x ∈ interior A := h_into_intA hx
    have hx_in_diff : x ∈ A ∧ x ∉ interior A := interior_subset hx
    exact (hx_in_diff.2 hx_in_intA).elim
  · -- Trivial inclusion `∅ ⊆ _`.
    exact Set.empty_subset _

theorem Topology.closure_union_subset {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    closure A ∪ closure B ⊆ closure (A ∪ B) := by
  intro x hx
  cases hx with
  | inl hA =>
      -- `A ⊆ A ∪ B`, so the monotonicity of `closure` yields the result.
      have h_subset : closure A ⊆ closure (A ∪ B) :=
        closure_mono (Set.subset_union_left : A ⊆ A ∪ B)
      exact h_subset hA
  | inr hB =>
      -- Symmetric argument for the second summand.
      have h_subset : closure B ⊆ closure (A ∪ B) :=
        closure_mono (Set.subset_union_right : B ⊆ A ∪ B)
      exact h_subset hB
